-Mz72oEkfnwbyNfz3yOd.text: Incident reported at Grand St NE & 26th Ave NE.

-Mz72oFtV4f_U13bCZjd.text: Firefighters are responding to an unconfirmed report of a structure fire.

-Mz75waKZibKOTT5_vUz.text: Firefighters confirm a heavy fire in the attic. Evacuation is underway.

-Mz76Bu-qot30hWG1O92.text: All units are evacuating the building due to the heavy fire and strong winds.

-Mz76HRaesoZZT6XK2FY.text: Firefighters advise there was a flashover in the attic.

-Mz76PTWPb77W4yR6kED.text: Firefighters are conducting a PAR to check for injuries among the firefighters.

-Mz76i75AeDYNs3eyAmq.text: Firefighters report there is heavy fire in the attic.

-Mz77AeNAK-vtZGrkrKW.text: One firefighter is being evaluated by medics.

-Mz77MOQXnwaFgrEOUgf.text: Firefighters report PAR was completed and there are no firefighters trapped inside of the building.

-Mz77TGEfnO869Si-Siw.text: Firefighters are working to contain the fire from the exterior of the building.

-Mz77Y0vPaVk4sUrHDY7.text: An additional ambulance has been requested.

-Mz77es76rrgmEEZNlKE.text: Firefighters advise all residents of the home exited the building.

-Mz77oNufjpEG6wLU2d1.text: Firefighters are dousing the fire with water.

-Mz78a5s7x11gwTvHOps.text: Firefighters have completed primary searches of the basement and the second floor. No one was trapped inside and there were no extensions of the fire in the basement.

-Mz7BGsGF9QfImRksNBE.text: After a search, firefighters report the attic is clear of any remaining fire.

-Mz7BXRYzbw3fKa1evFs.text: According to initial reports, the fire started from an extremely hot fire in the fireplace before the flashover occurred.

-Mz7Cj9kpz_pfeIqjzWC.text: According to an update from the Minneapolis Fire Department Twitter, the fire has been extinguished. Firefighters are still on scene searching for any hidden pockets of fire.

-Mz7D6sl64012yPZn8tt.text: Firefighter advise the fire is under control. No additional extensions of the fire were located.
